@majkshkurti maybe you can have a look again? I thought you once fixed this in #717.

The routing type for wheelchair should be passed like this as the profiles walking_wheelchair_standard and walking_wheelchair_electric are not existing in the backend. I fixed this for FFB-branch but still needs to be fixed in development.

`"walking_wheelchair": {
          "default": "",
          "options": [
            {
              "value": "",
              "speed": 3
            },
            {
              "value": "",
              "speed": 6
            }
          ]
        }
`

This error message should only pop up for the heatmaps "Walkability Population Index" and "Walkability". And not for "Area Isochrones" and "Population".

<img width="960" alt="error" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49870195/70986586-79596c00-20be-11ea-80d3-d9b36d0bb508.PNG">

@majkshkurti could you please adjust that?

We have to add the osm_humanized_opening_hours to the PostGIS-image. Naturally not a big deal, though there is an issue because the 'apt install postgresql11-pgrouting' automatically upgrades to pgrouting 3.0 Beta now (this was not the case when we build the image). As this is a major new release of pgrouting this is breaking some of our code. 

I think we need to install pgrouting from another source as the 'apt install postgresql11-pgrouting' does not allow you to specify a certain version. In worst case we have to compile it.

@majkshkurti for testing the opening_hours feature at the moment you have to manually install the python-library (sudo docker exec -it goat-database pip3 install osm_humanized_opening_hours)
